ki-o-rahi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the traditional game of rahi, a full contact tackling game played on a circular pitch.
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Each team has 10 or more players, or often played seven-a-side. Players generally run with the ball in hand, but kicking is also permitted. This game preceded rugby.
